stylometry: Some problems that come about when using nonlinear models is that it is more difficult to solve than a linear model.  When using conventional solver we have to be aware of the maximum and minimum aspect of the solver.  This could change the whole outcome.  Another thing is that we have to make sure that everything that is put into the solver table is correct such as the constraints and the cell that we are solving for (example max profit cell).  Back to using the solver with nonlinear models there may be problems such as different answers depending on where you start your changing cells.  If you start them at 1000 or if you start them at 100 because it is a nonlinear problem you may get a slightly different answer.
